result.execSummary:
Clayton D. Collins was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Clayton D. Collins was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Letter to Governor of WI with copy of Waiver of Extradition & Fugitive Complaint.

Defendant Clayton D. Collins in court, in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin appears by phone.  Circuit Court Judge, James Duvall & Court Reporter, Jane Krueger appear by phone from Buffalo County Courtroom.  Judge advises defendant of Warrant in State of Minnesota, extradition process.  Advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant waives right to an atty. and waives extradition.  Court finds defendant was advised of his rights to extradition, right to counsel, right to habeas corpus and he knowingly & voluntarily Waives Extradition.  Defendant remanded to the PCSD to be turned over forthwith to Winona, MN.
